29 f. ultimos orbis Britannos: cf. 4. 14, 47 remoti . . . Britanni. Catull. 11, 11 ultimi Britanni. Britain was practically a terra in- cognita to the Roman until the time of Claudius: the expeditions of Julius Caesar had had no per- manent result except to arouse a desire for Britain's conquest.
